article.headline: Lipscomb 71, Campbell 65 (OT)
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- James Poindexter scored 19 points as Lipscomb beat Campbell 71-65 in overtime Thursday night. A Labrian Lyons jumper tied the game at 55 with 1:31 left in regulation, but Campbell (2-22, 0-17 Atlantic Sun Conference) pushed it to overtime on a Comerlee Poole layup with 12 seconds left. Lipscomb (13-11, 8-9) went on an 11-1 run in overtime to take a 68-61 lead with 1:11 left. The run included three consecutive 3-pointers, the first two from Poindexter. The Fighting Camels took their first lead of the game, 24-23, early in the second half after holding Lipscomb scoreless in the final seven minutes of the first half. The Bisons' Eddie Ard blocked a school-record nine shots, and Brian Fisk scored 17 points. Campbell was led in scoring by Diego Aguiar and Ruell Pringle with 15 points each. Jake Wohlfeil added 11 points and Poole 10.
